time required: 20 minutes
---

Boil a full #kettle{}.

Peel and grate the @Garlic Clove{1}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}). Trim the @Green Beans{80%grams}, then cut into thirds.

Cut the @Lime{1/2}(cut into wedges).

Pour the boiled water for the sauce (@Water{150%ml}) into a #measuring jug{}. Pour the remaining boiled water into a #medium saucepan{} with @salt{1/2%tsp} and bring to the boil.

Add the @Egg Noodle Nest{125%grams} and cook until tender, ~{4%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #sieve{} and run under cold water to stop them sticking together.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of oil in a #large frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the @Diced British Chicken Breast{240%grams} to the pan and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Fry until golden brown on the outside and cooked through, ~{8-10%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging. It's cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Heat a drizzle of oil in another large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the @Vegetable Gyozas{1%pack} and fry until golden on the bottom, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Once golden, remove from the heat, then add 1 tbsp water to the pan. Pop back on medium-low heat and immediately cover with a #lid{} or some #foil{}. Cook until the gyozas are piping hot, ~{3-4%minutes}. Remove from the heat.

Meanwhile, in a #jug{} or #bowl{}, mix together the boiled water and @Sugar{1%tsp}, @Soy Sauce{15%ml}, @Peanut Butter{30%grams} and @Ketjap Manis{25%grams}.

> TIP: The peanut butter will loosen more when it warms up in the hot pan.

Once the chicken is cooked, add the @Yellow Thai Style Paste{45%grams}, green beans and garlic to the pan. Cook until fragrant, ~{1%minute}.

Add the cooked noodles and peanut sauce, stirring until well combined, ~{2-3%minutes}. Add a splash of water to loosen the sauce if needed.

Add a generous squeeze of lime juice. Taste and season with @salt{} and @pepper{} if needed.

Share your peanut noodles between your #bowls{}. Top with the veggie gyozas.

Serve with any remaining lime wedges alongside for squeezing over. Enjoy!